channel.title: push and pop Examples :: Introduction to Web Dev
channel.description: .push() And .pop() Examples .push() The general syntax for this method is: arrayName.push(item1, item2, ...)This method adds one or more items to the END of an array and returns the new length. The new items may be of any data type. Example let arr = ['a', 'b', 'c']; console.log(arr.push('d', 'f', 42)); console.log(arr);
